The full-scale M-COG system will use a 200-gallon receiver tank rated for 200 psig MAWP. The fill
schedule will follow the following fill control guidelines:
When tank pressure is <100 psig, production rate is nominal.
When tank pressure is between 101 125 psig, production rate is 50% nominal.
When tank pressure is between 126 - 150 psig, production rate is 10% nominal.
When tank pressure is between 151 175 psig, production rate is 2% nominal.
When tank pressure is > 175 psig, a normally controlled solenoid is powered on, and the
tank pressure is reduced until tank pressure is between 130 135 psig.
If product purity is >99.0%, the gas management control system shall record system operating
status as product purity ok and record this condition once every 10 minutes.
If product purity is <99.0%, the gas management control system shall record system operating
status as product purity <99.0% status, log processing operating parameters at 1 Hz frequency for
the 10 minutes prior to low purity status, divert oxygen from tank to vent, and conduct a controlled
shut down. Processing operating parameters shall be recorded at 0.1 Hz frequency during system
The gas management control system shall measure forward flow of oxygen from CFC to tank using
a delta pressure measurement across a flow restrictor in the oxygen delivery line. If dP trends
indicate leakage in the cell stack and reverse flow from the tank to the CFC oxygen generator, the
gas management control system shall issue a system leak status, log process operation
parameters for the 10 minutes prior to the fault, conduct a controlled shut down. Processing
parameters shall be recorded at 0.1 hz frequency during system shutdown.
a. Qty (1) set of sensing and control hardware components needed to measure oxygen product purity
and detecting low oxygen purity conditions.
b. Qty (1) set of sensing and control hardware components capable of measuring delivery tank
pressure and controlling M-COG oxygen production rate.
